Privacy Policy for Google Play Store

Effective date: April 20, 2023

This Privacy Policy outlines how Golden Reed - The KJV In Context Dictionary ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses information when you use our mobile application (the "App") available on the Google Play Store.

Information We Collect
We may collect the following information when you use our App:

Audio recordings: We may collect audio recordings from your device's microphone when you use certain features of our App that require permission to access your device's microphone.

Device information: We may collect information about your device, such as the operating system version, device type, and unique device identifiers.

Usage data: We may collect information about how you use our App, such as the features you use, the time and duration of your usage, and the frequency of your usage.

How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:

Provide and improve our App: We use your information to operate and maintain our App, to develop new features, and to improve the overall user experience.

Personalize your experience: We may use your information to tailor the content and features of our App to your preferences and interests.

Communicate with you: We may use your information to respond to your inquiries, to provide you with updates and notifications about our App, and to send you marketing communications that may be of interest to you.

Information Sharing and Disclosure
We may share your information with third parties in the following circumstances:

Service providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers who help us operate our App and provide you with our services.

Legal compliance: We may disclose your information if required by law or if we believe in good faith that such disclosure is necessary to comply with legal requirements, to protect our rights or property, or to ensure the safety of our users.

Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no data transmission over the internet or any wireless network can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the security of your information.

Your Rights
You may have certain rights with respect to your information, such as the right to access and update your information, the right to request that we delete your information, and the right to object to or restrict certain processing of your information. Please contact us using the information provided below to exercise these rights.

Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time by posting a new version on our website or within our App. You should review this Privacy Policy periodically for changes. If we make material changes to this Privacy Policy, we will provide notice to you in accordance with applicable laws.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at admin@trafficologyseo.com
